Samantha Power has been confirmed as the next U.S. Ambassador to the United Nations by a strong, bipartisan majority. President Obama is pleased with her confirmation and believes that her expertise in foreign policy and advocacy for human rights will make her a strong advocate for universal rights and U.S. national interests. The President is grateful that she will continue to be a member of his national security team and believes that under her leadership, the U.S. Mission to the UN will represent American diplomacy at its best.